name":"Giffard","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["Norman, English: (i) relationship name from the Continental Germanic personal name  <i>Gifard</i>. (ii) nickname, perhaps sometimes from Old French  <i>giffard</i> ‘chubby-cheeked, bloated’."],"variants":[{"name":"Jeffords","meanings":["English: variant of   Gifford  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>. This surname is now rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Jefford","meanings":["English:  see  Giffard  ."]},{"name":"Guiver","meanings":["English: (i) nickname, apparently from Middle English  <i>giver</i> ‘giver, donor, bestower’. (ii) variant of   Giffard   with voicing of /f/ to /v/ and loss of final  <i>-d</i>."]},{"name":"Gafford","meanings":["English (southeastern): assimilated form of <b>Gatford</b>, a name of various origins. In Sussex and Surrey it is perhaps a variant of the habitational name <b>Catford</b> from a place so called in Somerset. <b>Gatford</b> is also from the habitational names Gateford (in Worksop, Nottinghamshire) or Gateforth (near Selby, Yorkshire), both formed with Old English <i>gāt</i> ‘goat’ + <i>ford</i> ‘ford’, influenced by Old Norse <i>geit</i> ‘goat’.","Probably also an altered form of German <b>Gaffert</b>: habitational name from Gaffert near Köslin, Brandenburg, or from a personal name formed with Middle High German <i>gate</i> ‘fellow, companion’. The surname <i>Gaffert</i> is very rare in Germany.","English: perhaps an altered form of   Gatewood  , an occupational name for a ‘goatherd’ (Middle English <i>gate-werde</i>, Old English <i>gātweard</i>) or for a ‘gate keeper’ (Middle English <i>gateward</i>, Old English <i>ʒeatweard</i>, dialect <i>gātward</i>)."]},{"name":"Gifford","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of <b>Giffard</b>, either from the Middle English personal name <i>Gifard</i>, derived from an Old French name of this form deriving from ancient Germanic <i>geb-</i> ‘give, gift’ + <i>hard-</i> ‘hardy, brave’, or perhaps sometimes a nickname from Old French <i>gif(f)ard</i> ‘chubby-cheeked, bloated’."]},{"name":"Jefferd","meanings":["English:  see  Giffard  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When John Giffard was born in 1290, in Chillington, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, John Giffard, was 3 and his mother, Aveline de Courtenay, was 9. He had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Catherine Stafford. He died in 1371, in his hometown, at the age of 81."},"et":{"1290–1371":"1290–1371","1299–1361":"1299–1361","1316–1365":"1316–1365","1335–1378":"1335–1378","1340–Female":"1340–Surnud","1287–1323":"1287–1323","1281–1327":"1281–1327","December 1361":"detsember 1361","before 1311":"enne 1311","1340":"1340","1361":"1361","April 1323 or May 1323":"aprill 1323","1371":"1371","1281":"1281","1290":"1290","1316":"1316","1327":"1327","1335":"1335","27 April 1327":"27. aprill 1327","1323":"1323","1378":"1378","1365":"1365","1299":"1299","1287":"1287","Scotland, Scotland":"Scotland",", Gloucester, England":"Gloucester, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Middleton, Norfolk, England":"Middleton, Norfolk, England","Chillington, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Chillington, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Chillington, Staffordshire, England":"Chillington, Staffordshire, England","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1290–1371":"1290–1371","1299–1361":"1299–1361","1316–1365":"1316–1365","1335–1378":"1335–1378","1340–Female":"1340–Kuollut","1287–1323":"1287–1323","1281–1327":"1281–1327","December 1361":"joulukuu 1361","before 1311":"ennen vuotta 1311","1340":"1340","1361":"136